topic.title: Question about max_size
topic.body: After cloning this site, the max_size limit went from 1000000 to 20000. Does someone know how to switch it back? collins@zeroid.bit

3_1L8UURA9tgSn2XcRxtpCRJYCQm5S9ELh2Y.body:
The developer of zerotalk with images told me how to solve this problem. What a nice guy. 

1. Turn ZeroNet off 
2. In the folder of your website, browse to the file data/users/content.json 
3. Open it in a text editor 
4. Change "max_size": 20000 to the desired value (e.g. 100000000) 
5. Save the file 
6. Sign the changed file in the console: zeronet.py siteSign [yoursiteaddress] --inner_path data/users/content.json 
7. Start ZeroNet 
8. Done
